          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-05-26 14:18:18" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a surface of hard ground or stone where grain was threshed out, either by beating or having animals trample upon it</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>threshing floor</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>The meaning of ἅλων as ‘threshing floor’ forms the basis for the figurative extension of meaning (a metonymy) referring to the threshed grain still lying on the threshing floor (see {D:3.43}). The meaning may be made clear by rendering ‘to thresh out completely all of the grain.’ On the other hand, it is possible to interpret ἅλων in {S:04000301200022} in a literal sense and translate ‘he will clean up his threshing floor,’ that is, by gathering up the grain and getting rid of the straw and chaff.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
